Business is not going well for everyone on Durban's promenade. The beaches have reopened after the public holiday closure. But a rickshaw puller says they don't know who to turn to. eNCA's Lethiwe Mdluli has more. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - Tourists are again flocking to Durban's beaches. But business is not going well for everyone on the promenade. A rickshaw puller said COVID-19 has really affected them badly. READ: Durban expects buzzing beaches as tourists make up for lost time "Business is not going well. We usually make a lot of money during the holidays but now with COVID-19, we are not doing well," said Khetha Nxumalo. "This is our way of making a living and now we don't know who to turn to." * eNCA's Lethiwe Mdluli reports.